$ R: Graphical device parameters

Each → development/languages/R/graphics/device[device] has a its own set of *graphical parameters* which can be set or queried with → development/languages/R/functions/par[`par()`].

Some` (all?) graphical paraemters are:
table` { lll
  `adj` ☰ Justification of text strings in → development/languages/R/functions/text[`text`], `mtext` and `title` ☰ A value between `0` and `1`.
  `ann` ☰ ☰ `TRUE`, `FALSE`0
  `ask` ☰ Ask a user of an interactive session before a new figure is drawn ☰ `TRUE`, `FALSE`
  `bg` ☰ Background color (compare `fg` and `col`) ☰ 
  `bty` ☰ Type of `box` ☰ 
  `cex` ☰ Magnification of text and symbols, relative to default ☰ numerical value
  `cex.axis` ☰ ☰ 
  `cex.lab` ☰ ☰ 
  `cex.main` ☰ ☰ 
  `cex.sub` ☰ ☰ 
  `cin` ☰ Character size in inches, read only (compare `cra`) ☰ 
  `col` ☰ Default color (compare `bg`) ☰ 
  `col.axis` ☰ ☰ 
  `col.lab` ☰ ☰ 
  `col.main` ☰ ☰ 
  `cra` ☰ Character size in pixels (ra = raster). Compare with `cin` ☰ 
  `crt` ☰ Rotation of characters in degrees ☰ Numerical value. Should be multiples of 90.
  `csi` ☰ Height of character in inches. Same as `par(cin)[2]`. Read only. ☰ 
  `cxy` ☰ ☰ 
  `din` ☰ Device dimensions in inches. Read only. See also → development/languages/R/functions/dev_size[`dev.size()`] ☰ 
  `err` (apparently not implemented) ☰ ☰ 
  `family` ☰ → design/font/font[Font] family ☰ ``, `serif`, `sans`, `mono`, Hershey font families …
  `fg` ☰ Forground color. Compare with `bg` ☰ 
  `fig` ☰ ☰ 
  `fin` ☰ ☰ 
  `font` ☰ Compare with `family` ☰ `1` = normal, `2` = bold`, `3` = italic, `4` = bold italic
  `font.axis` ☰ ☰ 
  `font.lab` ☰ ☰ 
  `font.main` ☰ ☰ 
  `font.sub` ☰ ☰ 
  `lab` ☰ Annotation of axes ☰ `c(x, y, len)`
  `las` ☰ Style of axis labels ☰ `0`: parallel, `1`: horizontal, `2`: perpendicular, `3`: vertical
  `lend` ☰ Line end style ☰ `0` = `round` / `1` = `butt` / `2` = `square`
  `lheight` ☰ Line hight multiplier ☰ 
  `ljoin` ☰ Line join style ☰ 
  `lmitre` ☰ Line mitre limit ☰ 
  `lty` ☰ Line type ☰ 
  `lwd` ☰ Line width ☰ 
  `mai` ☰ Margin in inches ☰ 
  `mar` ☰ ☰ `c(bottom, left, top, right)`
  `mex` ☰ Character size expansion ☰ 
  `mfcol, mfrow` ☰ Draw plots in a «table» of mfcol times mfrow columns ☰ 
  `mfg` ☰ ☰ 
  `mgp` ☰ Margin line for axis title in `mex` units ☰ 
  `mkh` ☰ ☰ 
  `new` ☰ If `FALSE`, `plot.new()` will not clean the frame ☰ 
  `oma` ☰ ☰ 
  `omd` ☰ ☰ 
  `omi` ☰ ☰ 
  `page` ☰ ☰ 
  `pch` ☰ Specify point type for plotting ☰ 
  `pin` ☰ ☰ 
  `plt` ☰ ☰ 
  `ps` ☰ ☰ 
  `pty` ☰ Type of plot region ☰ `s`: square, `m`: maximal
  `smo` ☰ Unimplmeneted ☰ 
  `srt` ☰ Degrees of String rotation ☰ 
  `tck` ☰ Lenght of tick marks ☰ 
  `tcl` ☰ ☰ 
  `usr` ☰ Extrems of user coordinates ☰ 
  `xaxp` ☰ ☰ 
  `xaxs` ☰ ☰ 
  `xaxt` ☰ ☰ 
  `xlog` ☰ If `TRUE`, a logarthmic scale is used ☰ 
  `xpd` ☰ ☰ 
  `yaxp` ☰ ☰ 
  `yaxs` ☰ ☰ 
  `yaxt` ☰ ☰ 
  `ylbias` ☰ ☰ 
  `ylog` ☰ ☰ 
table` }




